title: crystalCallDialogue
---
Sky: <i>The Mother Crystal called for me, I should probably go there.</i>
===

title: tutorialStartDialogue
position: -87,210
---
<<once>>
Mother Crystal: Child of the sky… so you’ve answered my plea.

Sky: What’s this all about? What’s going on?

Mother Crystal: I will provide you with the answers you seek, shall you prove yourself worthy… but first.

//(The camera pans over a bit to reveal a simple puzzle in front of Sky, and a gold rune circle, which begins to glow)

Sky: A puzzle? What does that have to do with, well, everything?

Mother Crystal: This is a rune circle. They can be found throughout Ethor wherever you may find empty void or hazardous terrain.

Mother Crystal: In order to traverse such obstacles, you will need to solve a puzzle that is tied to the rune circle.

Mother Crystal: Consider this first one a mere test of wits. If you may, please interact with the rune circle.

<b>Interact with the Rune Circle</b>
<<endonce>>
===

title: tutorialPuzzle1Dialogue
---
<<once>>
Mother Crystal: Upon stepping inside a rune circle, you will enter a state which we shall call “Puzzle Mode.”

Mother Crystal: Your view will shift, revealing what you need in order to proceed.

Mother Crystal: Only through here will you be able to create the desirable route using nearby terrain at your disposal.

Mother Crystal: While in this state, you will be confined to orthogonal movement.

Mother Crystal: On your right, you’ll find a hand of “Rune Cards.”

Mother Crystal: These Rune Cards carry the essence of my power, allowing you to move and shape the terrain.

Mother Crystal: Now go on… select a Rune Card and forge your path.

Mother Crystal: Then choose a tile to utilize its power. Pick the one that will help you form a bridge! If you mess up, you can always reset a puzzle.
<<endonce>>
===

title: postPuzzle1Dialogue
---
<<once>>
Mother Crystal: Splendid! Now, there’s a vital piece of information I must bestow upon you.

Mother Crystal: Playing a Rune Card will expend a singular point of Mana, a finite resource representing your magical reserve for each puzzle.

Mother Crystal: The amount of Mana at your disposal, alongside the Rune Cards and their effects are dependent on the puzzle.

Mother Crystal: In some instances, you may not even need to play every card!

Mother Crystal: The next trial, albeit challenging, shall be done without my guidance.

<b>Complete the next puzzle!</b>
<<endonce>>
===

title: tutorialPuzzle2Dialogue
---
<<once>>
Mother Crystal: Child, I forgot to tell you a couple things. 

Mother Crystal: You may exit a puzzle whenever you please. However, doing so will revert all of your progress.

Mother Crystal: (Most importantly, all of this information can be found in your Settings).
<<endonce>>
===

title: postPuzzle2Dialogue
---
<<once>>
Mother Crystal: Astonishing! Child, you truly have proven yourself worthy

Sky: Piece of cake! Does this mean I’m worthy of answers?

Mother Crystal: I’m an entity of my word. Listen, young one, this is of utmost importance…

Mother Crystal: Long ago, my light shone freely throughout all the land. The people of Ethor utilized my power, and the world flourished. 

Mother Crystal: But as people’s appetite for more power grew, so did the imbalance, and the threat of calamity arose.

Mother Crystal: In order to prevent such a catastrophe, I did what I must; I fractured the land and scattered my power.”

Mother Crystal: Each island carries a fraction of my essence, but their crystals are frail, leaving their lands in distress.

Mother Crystal: Much time has passed, and now the islands are crying for a hero to prevent the collapse of Ethor.

Mother Crystal: Sky…

Mother Crystal: You have proven yourself worthy of being that hero.

Sky: I’m… that hero…?

Sky: And I have to go out there, to all the islands?

Mother Crystal: Yes. Though, don’t fear. I shall not send you forth unprepared. I will bestow my blessing upon you.

Sky: What’s this? What’s happening to me?!

Mother Crystal: Don’t fret, child. This will not put you in any harm.

Mother Crystal: I have simply reserved your body as a vessel for my powers.

Mother Crystal: With my power in tow, the barriers that once sealed the lands shall yield to you, and the paths to the lands shall reveal themselves.

Sky: Will this really allow me to go to other islands?

Mother Crystal: Yes, child. The path is yours to walk… but my blessing alone is not enough for you to traverse the skies. 

Sky: Wait, what? Then, how do I get there? I thought travel between the islands was impossible…

Mother Crystal: It is for those who do not have my blessing. Fear not, child. Your means of transportation lies nearby, far closer than you imagine. You shall find that it behaves differently with your newfound power. 

Mother Crystal: Now, with my blessing in hand, the journey is yours to begin. 

Mother Crystal: Go forth, child of the sky, and let courage guide you where my light alone cannot.

Mother Crystal: You are to return here at the conclusion of your travels. May Ethor smile upon you.

Sky: <i>Transportation?</i> 

Sky: <i>Right! Dad’s airship! I’ve gotta go talk to him!</i>

<<toggleExclamation Cumulus>>
<<enableInvisWall AirshipColliderWall>>
<<endonce>>
===

title: getSentOffDialogue
---
Cumulus: Oh, Sky, one more thing!

Sky: What’s that, Dad?

Cumulus: I love you! Be safe please!

Sky: Don’t worry about me, Dad! I love you too!

Cumulus: Go make all of Ethor proud!

Sky: You know I will!
===